Azure AKS Cluster Deployment

This folder contains Terraform scripts to deploy an Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) cluster.

Deployment Steps:

Clone the repository.
Navigate to the "aks-cluster" directory.
Modify variables in variables.tf as needed.
Run terraform init to initialize the project.
Execute terraform plan to review the deployment plan.
Apply changes with terraform apply.
Confirm the deployment by typing yes.
Folder Structure:

main.tf: Configurations for AKS cluster deployment.
variables.tf: Definition of input variables.
outputs.tf: Outputs to display after deployment.
terraform.tfvars: Option to set default variable values.
Ensure proper authentication to your Azure account using the Azure CLI or Service Principal before running Terraform commands.